## Server-Side Authentication

### 1. Protected API Routes

Create protected API routes in `server/api/v1/`:

```typescript
// server/api/v1/protected/profile.get.ts
export default defineEventHandler(async (event) => {
  // Get session from headers
  const session = await auth.api.getSession({
    headers: event.headers,
  });

  if (!session?.session) {
    throw createError({
      statusCode: 401,
      statusMessage: "Unauthorized",
    });
  }

  // Return user profile data
  return {
    user: session.user,
    session: session.session,
  };
});
```

### 2. Server Middleware for Authentication

Create `server/middleware/auth.ts`:

```typescript
export default defineEventHandler(async (event) => {
  // Skip non-protected routes
  if (!event.node.req.url?.startsWith("/api/v1/protected")) {
    return;
  }

  const session = await auth.api.getSession({
    headers: event.headers,
  });

  if (!session?.session) {
    throw createError({
      statusCode: 401,
      statusMessage: "Authentication required",
    });
  }

  // Add session to event context
  event.context.session = session;
});
```

## Environment Configuration

### 1. Environment Variables

Create `.env` file:

```bash
# Database
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/myapp"

# Better Auth
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET="your-super-secret-key"
BETTER_AUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# Social Providers
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID="your-github-client-id"
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET="your-github-client-secret"
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="your-google-client-id"
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="your-google-client-secret"

# Email Service (optional)
SMTP_HOST="smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT="587"
SMTP_USER="your-email@gmail.com"
SMTP_PASS="your-app-password"
```

### 2. Nuxt Configuration

Update `nuxt.config.ts`:

```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  // Nuxt 4 configuration
  srcDir: "app",

  runtimeConfig: {
    // Server-side environment variables
    betterAuthSecret: process.env.BETTER_AUTH_SECRET,
    githubClientSecret: process.env.GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET,
    googleClientSecret: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET,

    // Public environment variables
    public: {
      betterAuthUrl: process.env.BETTER_AUTH_URL || "http://localhost:3000",
      siteUrl: process.env.NUXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL || "http://localhost:3000",
    },
  },

  // Enable SSR for better SEO and performance
  ssr: true,

  // CSS framework
  css: ["~/assets/css/main.css"],

  // Modules
  modules: ["@unocss/nuxt", "@primevue/nuxt-module", "@pinia/nuxt"],

  // Nitro configuration for Better Auth
  nitro: {
    experimental: {
      wasm: true,
    },
  },
});
```

## Database Setup

### 1. PostgreSQL Configuration

Better Auth works directly with PostgreSQL Pool without requiring an ORM. The database connection is configured in the server setup:

```typescript
// Already configured in server/utils/auth.ts
database: new Pool({
  connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URL,
})
```

### 2. Database Migration

```bash
# Run Better Auth migrations to create required tables
pnpx @better-auth/cli migrate

# Or generate SQL schema file for manual setup
pnpx @better-auth/cli generate

# The generated schema can be found in the output directory
# and manually applied to your database
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Security Considerations

- Always use HTTPS in production
- Set secure cookie flags in production
- Implement rate limiting
- Validate and sanitize user inputs
- Use environment variables for secrets

### 2. Error Handling

```typescript
// app/composables/useAuthError.ts
export const useAuthError = () => {
  const handleAuthError = (error: any) => {
    if (error.statusCode === 401) {
      // Redirect to login
      navigateTo("/auth/signin");
      return;
    }

    if (error.statusCode === 403) {
      // Show forbidden message
      throw createError({
        statusCode: 403,
        statusMessage: "Access denied",
      });
    }

    // Log other errors
    console.error("Auth error:", error);
    throw error;
  };

  return { handleAuthError };
};
```

### 3. Performance Optimization

- Use `useLazyFetch` for session data
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Optimize database queries
- Use server-side rendering where appropriate

